402	
403	## 2. Anatomy
404	
405	```text
406	PasswordInput
407	├── Root               <div>     data-ars-scope="password-input" data-ars-part="root"
408	├── Label              <label>   data-ars-part="label"
409	├── Input         [A]  <input>   data-ars-part="input" (type="password"|"text")
410	├── Toggle             <button>  data-ars-part="toggle" (aria-label)
411	├── Description        <div>     data-ars-part="description" (optional)
412	└── ErrorMessage       <div>     data-ars-part="error-message" (optional)
413	```
414	
415	| Part         | Element    | Key Attributes                                             |
416	| ------------ | ---------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
417	| Root         | `<div>`    | `data-ars-scope="password-input"`, `data-ars-state`        |
418	| Label        | `<label>`  | `for` points to Input                                      |
419	| Input        | `<input>`  | `type="password"` or `"text"`, `aria-labelledby`           |
420	| Toggle       | `<button>` | `aria-label` (dynamic: show/hide), `type="button"`         |
421	| Description  | `<div>`    | Help text; linked via `aria-describedby` (optional)        |
422	| ErrorMessage | `<div>`    | Validation error; linked via `aria-describedby` (optional) |
423	
424	- **Input** renders as `type="password"` when masked, `type="text"` when visible.
425	- **Toggle** is a button that switches visibility. It displays an eye icon (open/closed)
426	  managed by the consumer or a default icon slot.
427	
428	## 3. Accessibility
429	
430	### 3.1 ARIA Roles, States, and Properties
431	
432	| Property           | Element | Value                                                  |
433	| ------------------ | ------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
434	| `type`             | Input   | `"password"` (Masked) or `"text"` (Visible)            |
435	| `aria-label`       | Toggle  | Dynamic: `show_password_label` / `hide_password_label` |
436	| `aria-required`    | Input   | Present when `required=true`                           |
437	| `aria-invalid`     | Input   | Present when `invalid=true`                            |
438	| `aria-labelledby`  | Input   | Points to Label id                                     |
439	| `aria-describedby` | Input   | Points to Description + ErrorMessage ids               |
440	
441	- Dynamic toggle label communicates state; `aria-pressed` would be redundant and contradictory.
442	
443	### 3.2 Keyboard Interaction
444	
445	| Key     | Context        | Action            |
446	| ------- | -------------- | ----------------- |
447	| `Enter` | Toggle focused | Toggle visibility |
448	| `Space` | Toggle focused | Toggle visibility |
449	
450	> The toggle button is in the tab order (`tabindex="0"`), so users can
451	> Tab from the password input to the toggle button and activate it with Enter or Space.
452	
453	### 3.3 Screen Reader Behavior
454	
455	- The toggle button announces its current label (from `messages.show_password_label` or
456	  `messages.hide_password_label`) so users know whether the password is revealed.
457	- Toggling visibility does not move focus — the input retains focus and screen readers
458	  announce the type change.
459	
460	### 3.4 IME Composition Handling
461	
462	See [IME Composition Protocol](./_category.md#ime-composition-protocol) for input method editor behavior
463	during text composition. PasswordInput wraps a TextField and inherits its IME composition
464	handling: during `compositionstart`...`compositionend`, custom keyboard handlers are suppressed
465	and the final composed value is applied as a single update on `compositionend`.
466	
467	## 4. Internationalization
468	
469	### 4.1 Messages
470	
471	Toggle button labels are provided through the `Messages` struct:
472	
473	- `show_password_label` — displayed when password is masked (default: "Show password")
474	- `hide_password_label` — displayed when password is visible (default: "Hide password")
475	
476	See §1.4 for the `Messages` struct definition and `Default` implementation.
477	
478	- `placeholder` is localized by the consumer.
479	- RTL: Input text direction follows the document locale. The toggle button position is
480	  handled via CSS logical properties (`inset-inline-end`).
481	
482	## 5. Form Integration
483	
484	- **Hidden input**: The `Input` part is the native `<input>` element and participates directly in form submission via its `name` attribute. No separate hidden input is needed.
485	- **Validation states**: `aria-invalid="true"` on the Input when `invalid=true`. The `ErrorMessage` part is linked via `aria-describedby`.
486	- **Error message association**: `aria-describedby` on Input points to `Description` (when present) and `ErrorMessage` (when invalid).
487	- **Required**: `aria-required="true"` on Input.
488	- **Reset behavior**: On form reset, the adapter restores `value` to `default_value` and `visible` to `default_visible`.
489	- **Disabled/readonly propagation**: When inside a `Field` or `Fieldset`, the adapter merges `disabled`/`readonly` from `FieldCtx` per `07-forms.md` §12.6.
490	
491	## 6. Library Parity
492	
493	> Compared against: Ark UI (`PasswordInput`), Radix UI (`PasswordToggleField` preview).
494	
495	### 6.1 Props
496	
497	| Feature                  | ars-ui                         | Ark UI                   | Radix UI                  | Notes                     |
498	| ------------------------ | ------------------------------ | ------------------------ | ------------------------- | ------------------------- |
499	| Controlled value         | `value: Option<String>`        | --                       | --                        | ars-ui adds value control |
500	| Default value            | `default_value: String`        | --                       | --                        | ars-ui adds value control |
501	| Disabled                 | `disabled: bool`               | `disabled`               | --                        | Ark parity                |
502	| Required                 | `required: bool`               | `required`               | --                        | Ark parity                |
503	| Invalid                  | `invalid: bool`                | `invalid`                | --                        | Ark parity                |
504	| Read-only                | `readonly: bool`               | `readOnly`               | --                        | Ark parity                |
505	| Default visible          | `default_visible: bool`        | `defaultVisible`         | `defaultVisible`          | Full parity               |
506	| Controlled visible       | --                             | `visible`                | `visible`                 | See note below            |
507	| Autocomplete             | `autocomplete: Option<String>` | `autoComplete`           | `autoComplete` (on Input) | Full parity               |
508	| Form name                | `name: Option<String>`         | `name`                   | `name`                    | Full parity               |
509	| Form ID                  | `form: Option<String>`         | --                       | --                        | ars-ui enhancement        |
510	| Placeholder              | `placeholder: Option<String>`  | --                       | --                        | ars-ui enhancement        |
511	| Ignore password managers | --                             | `ignorePasswordManagers` | --                        | Ark-only feature          |
512	
513	**Gaps:**
514	
515	- **Controlled visibility**: Ark UI supports `visible: boolean` for controlled visibility state. ars-ui currently uses `default_visible` + `ToggleVisibility`/`SetVisibility` events, which achieves the same effect through the adapter's `on_visibility_change` callback. Not a functional gap since the adapter can wire controlled visibility through event callbacks.
516	
517	### 6.2 Anatomy
518	
519	| Part         | ars-ui         | Ark UI              | Radix UI      | Notes                  |
520	| ------------ | -------------- | ------------------- | ------------- | ---------------------- |
521	| Root         | `Root`         | `Root`              | `Root`        | Full parity            |
522	| Label        | `Label`        | `Label`             | --            | Ark parity             |
523	| Input        | `Input`        | `Input`             | `Input`       | Full parity            |
524	| Toggle       | `Toggle`       | `VisibilityTrigger` | `Toggle`      | Full parity            |
525	| Indicator    | --             | `Indicator`         | `Slot`/`Icon` | See note below         |
526	| Control      | --             | `Control`           | --            | Ark layout wrapper     |
527	| Description  | `Description`  | --                  | --            | ars-ui form-field part |
528	| ErrorMessage | `ErrorMessage` | --                  | --            | ars-ui form-field part |
529	
530	**Gaps:** None material. Ark's `Indicator` shows different content for visible/hidden states. In ars-ui, the Toggle button's children render conditionally based on `data-ars-state` (the same pattern). Radix's `Slot`/`Icon` serve the same purpose.
531	
532	### 6.3 Events
533	
534	| Callback           | ars-ui             | Ark UI               | Radix UI            | Notes       |
535	| ------------------ | ------------------ | -------------------- | ------------------- | ----------- |
536	| Visibility changed | `ToggleVisibility` | `onVisibilityChange` | `onVisiblityChange` | Full parity |
537	
538	**Gaps:** None.
539	
540	### 6.4 Features
541	
542	| Feature                  | ars-ui | Ark UI | Radix UI |
543	| ------------------------ | ------ | ------ | -------- |
544	| Show/hide toggle         | Yes    | Yes    | Yes      |
545	| Autocomplete hint        | Yes    | Yes    | Yes      |
546	| Form integration         | Yes    | Yes    | --       |
547	| Ignore password managers | --     | Yes    | --       |
548	
549	**Gaps:** None material. Ark's `ignorePasswordManagers` is a niche feature that blocks browser password manager autofill; ars-ui consumers can set `autocomplete: "off"` for a similar effect.
550	
551	### 6.5 Summary
552	
553	- **Overall:** Full parity with both reference libraries.
554	- **Divergences:** ars-ui adds value control (`value`/`default_value`) and form-field parts (Description, ErrorMessage) not present in either reference. Ark's `Indicator` pattern is achieved via conditional rendering on the Toggle button in ars-ui.
555	- **Recommended additions:** None.
556

