487	## 3. Accessibility
488	
489	### 3.1 ARIA Roles, States, and Properties
490	
491	| Property           | Element       | Value                                      |
492	| ------------------ | ------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
493	| `role`             | Root          | `search` (landmark)                        |
494	| `type`             | Input         | `"search"`                                 |
495	| `aria-busy`        | Root          | Present when `loading=true`                |
496	| `aria-invalid`     | Input         | Present when `invalid=true`                |
497	| `required`         | Input         | Present when `required=true` (native attr) |
498	| `aria-labelledby`  | Input         | Points to Label id                         |
499	| `aria-describedby` | Input         | Points to Description + ErrorMessage       |
500	| `aria-label`       | ClearTrigger  | From `messages.clear_label`                |
501	| `aria-label`       | SubmitTrigger | From `messages.submit_label`               |
502	
503	### 3.2 Keyboard Interaction
504	
505	| Key    | Action                              |
506	| ------ | ----------------------------------- |
507	| Enter  | Submit search query                 |
508	| Escape | Clear input                         |
509	| Tab    | Navigate between input and triggers |
510	
511	### 3.3 Keyboard Event Propagation in Nested Components
512	
513	When `SearchInput` is nested inside a parent component that also handles keyboard events (e.g., `Combobox`), event propagation must be carefully managed:
514	
515	**Rule**: `SearchInput` calls `stopPropagation()` **only** for keys it actually handles (Enter, Escape). It MUST NOT call `stopPropagation()` for keys it does not handle (ArrowUp, ArrowDown, Home, End, etc.), allowing the parent component to process them.
516	
517	**IME composition during nesting**: SearchInput emits `on_change` during active IME composition with the `is_composing: true` flag set in context. Parent components (e.g., Combobox) MUST check `search_input_ctx.is_composing` before filtering — when `true`, skip filtering to avoid showing results for incomplete CJK input.
518	
519	### 3.4 Browser SearchBox Integration
520	
521	When used with dropdown-style results (e.g., paired with a Listbox for suggestions), the following ARIA attributes are mandatory on the Input part:
522	
523	- `aria-controls`: Points to the results container element ID.
524	- `aria-expanded`: `"true"` when the results dropdown is visible, `"false"` otherwise.
525	- `autocomplete="off"`: Prevents browser autofill from interfering with custom results.
526	- `role="combobox"`: When paired with a results dropdown, overrides the implicit role.
527	
528	When SearchInput is used standalone (no dropdown), these attributes are not required.
529	
530	### 3.5 Autocomplete Results Announcement
531	
532	When paired with a results dropdown, the adapter MUST announce result counts to screen reader users via a live region, debounced by at least 300ms:
533	
534	- `"{N} results available"` when results arrive.
535	- `"No results available"` when the query returns no matches.
536	- The live region uses `aria-live="polite"` and `aria-atomic="true"`.
537	
538	## 4. Internationalization
539	
540	- `placeholder` localized by consumer ("Search...", "Rechercher...", etc.).
541	- `aria-label` for `ClearTrigger` and `SubmitTrigger` localized via `Messages`.
542	- RTL: Input text direction follows locale; icon positions may swap (CSS handles this).
543	
544	### 4.1 IME Composition Handling
545	
546	`SearchInput` tracks `is_composing: bool` in Context. During composition:
547	
548	- `Event::Change` still updates `ctx.value` for display, but the `on_change` callback and debounce timer are NOT triggered.
549	- After `compositionend`, the adapter fires a final `Event::Change` with the committed text, which triggers normal filter/debounce processing.
550	
551	See [IME Composition Protocol](./_category.md#ime-composition-protocol).
552	
553	### 4.2 Clear Event and Debounce Interaction
554	
555	When the user triggers the clear action:
556	
557	1. Any pending debounce timer is immediately cancelled.
558	2. `on_change("")` is emitted synchronously — bypasses debounce delay entirely.
559	3. A `debounce_ms` value of `Some(0)` is treated as `Some(1)` to prevent microtask-level race conditions.
560	
561	## 5. Form Integration
562	
563	- **Hidden input**: The `Input` part is the native `<input type="search">` and participates directly in form submission via its `name` attribute.
564	- **Validation states**: `aria-invalid="true"` on the Input when `invalid=true`. Native `required` attribute on Input when `required=true`. The `ErrorMessage` part is linked via `aria-describedby`.
565	- **Error message association**: `aria-describedby` on Input points to `Description` (when present) and `ErrorMessage` (when invalid).
566	- **Reset behavior**: On form reset, the adapter restores `value` to `default_value` and transitions to Idle.
567	- **Disabled/readonly propagation**: When inside a `Field` or `Fieldset`, the adapter merges `disabled`/`readonly` from `FieldCtx` per `07-forms.md` §12.6.
568	
569	## 6. Library Parity
570	
571	> Compared against: React Aria (`SearchField`).
572	>
573	> Note: Ark UI and Radix UI have no dedicated search input component.
574	
575	### 6.1 Props
576	
577	| Feature          | ars-ui                        | React Aria     | Notes              |
578	| ---------------- | ----------------------------- | -------------- | ------------------ |
579	| Controlled value | `value: Option<String>`       | `value`        | Full parity        |
580	| Default value    | `default_value: String`       | `defaultValue` | Full parity        |
581	| Disabled         | `disabled: bool`              | `isDisabled`   | Full parity        |
582	| Read-only        | `readonly: bool`              | `isReadOnly`   | Full parity        |
583	| Required         | `required: bool`              | `isRequired`   | Full parity        |
584	| Invalid          | `invalid: bool`               | `isInvalid`    | Full parity        |
585	| Placeholder      | `placeholder: Option<String>` | `placeholder`  | Full parity        |
586	| Form name        | `name: Option<String>`        | `name`         | Full parity        |
587	| Form ID          | `form: Option<String>`        | `form`         | Full parity        |
588	| Debounce         | `debounce_ms: Option<u32>`    | --             | ars-ui enhancement |
589	
590	**Gaps:** None.
591	
592	### 6.2 Anatomy
593	
594	| Part             | ars-ui             | React Aria          | Notes              |
595	| ---------------- | ------------------ | ------------------- | ------------------ |
596	| Root             | `Root`             | `SearchField`       | Full parity        |
597	| Label            | `Label`            | `Label`             | Full parity        |
598	| Input            | `Input`            | `Input`             | Full parity        |
599	| ClearTrigger     | `ClearTrigger`     | `Button` (clear)    | Full parity        |
600	| SubmitTrigger    | `SubmitTrigger`    | --                  | ars-ui enhancement |
601	| LoadingIndicator | `LoadingIndicator` | --                  | ars-ui enhancement |
602	| Description      | `Description`      | `Text[description]` | Full parity        |
603	| ErrorMessage     | `ErrorMessage`     | `FieldError`        | Full parity        |
604	
605	**Gaps:** None.
606	
607	### 6.3 Events
608	
609	| Callback      | ars-ui           | React Aria         | Notes       |
610	| ------------- | ---------------- | ------------------ | ----------- |
611	| Value changed | `Change(String)` | `onChange`         | Full parity |
612	| Submit        | `Submit`         | `onSubmit`         | Full parity |
613	| Clear         | `Clear`          | `onClear`          | Full parity |
614	| Focus         | `Focus`/`Blur`   | `onFocus`/`onBlur` | Full parity |
615	
616	**Gaps:** None.
617	
618	### 6.4 Features
619	
620	| Feature         | ars-ui | React Aria |
621	| --------------- | ------ | ---------- |
622	| Clear on Escape | Yes    | Yes        |
623	| Submit on Enter | Yes    | Yes        |
624	| Loading state   | Yes    | --         |
625	| Debounce        | Yes    | --         |
626	| IME composition | Yes    | Yes        |
627	| `type="search"` | Yes    | Yes        |
628	
629	**Gaps:** None.
630	
631	### 6.5 Summary
632	
633	- **Overall:** Full parity with React Aria SearchField.
634	- **Divergences:** ars-ui adds a loading/searching state, debounce support, submit trigger, and loading indicator not present in React Aria.
