612	
613	## 2. Anatomy
614	
615	```text
616	NumberInput
617	├── Root               <div>     data-ars-scope="number-input" data-ars-part="root"
618	├── Label              <label>   data-ars-part="label"
619	├── Input         [A]  <input>   data-ars-part="input" (role="spinbutton")
620	├── IncrementTrigger   <button>  data-ars-part="increment-trigger" (optional)
621	├── DecrementTrigger   <button>  data-ars-part="decrement-trigger" (optional)
622	├── Description        <div>     data-ars-part="description" (optional)
623	└── ErrorMessage       <div>     data-ars-part="error-message" (optional)
624	```
625	
626	| Part             | Element    | Key Attributes                                             |
627	| ---------------- | ---------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
628	| Root             | `<div>`    | `data-ars-scope="number-input"`, `data-ars-state`          |
629	| Label            | `<label>`  | `for` points to Input                                      |
630	| Input            | `<input>`  | `role="spinbutton"`, `aria-valuenow/min/max/text`          |
631	| IncrementTrigger | `<button>` | `aria-label`, disabled at max boundary (optional)          |
632	| DecrementTrigger | `<button>` | `aria-label`, disabled at min boundary (optional)          |
633	| Description      | `<div>`    | Help text; linked via `aria-describedby` (optional)        |
634	| ErrorMessage     | `<div>`    | Validation error; linked via `aria-describedby` (optional) |
635	
636	**Press-and-hold**: When the user holds a stepper button, the adapter starts a repeat timer
637	(initial delay 400ms, then repeat every 60ms) sending `Event::Increment` or
638	`Event::Decrement`. The timer is cancelled on pointerup or pointerleave.
639	
640	## 3. Accessibility
641	
642	### 3.1 ARIA Roles, States, and Properties
643	
644	| Property           | Element | Value                                    |
645	| ------------------ | ------- | ---------------------------------------- |
646	| `role`             | Input   | `spinbutton`                             |
647	| `aria-valuenow`    | Input   | Current numeric value                    |
648	| `aria-valuemin`    | Input   | Minimum value (when finite)              |
649	| `aria-valuemax`    | Input   | Maximum value (when finite)              |
650	| `aria-valuetext`   | Input   | Locale-formatted value string            |
651	| `aria-required`    | Input   | Present when `required=true`             |
652	| `aria-invalid`     | Input   | Present when `invalid=true`              |
653	| `aria-labelledby`  | Input   | Points to Label id                       |
654	| `aria-describedby` | Input   | Points to Description + ErrorMessage ids |
655	
656	### 3.2 Keyboard Interaction
657	
658	| Key            | Action                     |
659	| -------------- | -------------------------- |
660	| ArrowUp        | Increment by step          |
661	| ArrowDown      | Decrement by step          |
662	| PageUp         | Increment by large step    |
663	| PageDown       | Decrement by large step    |
664	| Home           | Set to minimum             |
665	| End            | Set to maximum             |
666	| Tab            | Move focus                 |
667	| Ctrl+V / Cmd+V | Paste (locale-aware parse) |
668	
669	### 3.3 Paste Event Handling
670	
671	When the user pastes content into the NumberInput, the adapter intercepts the `paste` event:
672	
673	1. **Extract clipboard text**: Read plain-text content from the clipboard.
674	2. **Strip whitespace**: Trim leading/trailing whitespace.
675	3. **Locale-aware parse**: Pass the trimmed text through `number::Formatter::parse()` using the resolved locale. This handles locale-specific decimal separators, grouping separators, currency symbols, and percentage signs.
676	4. **Validation**: If `parse()` returns `Ok(value)`: clamp to `[min, max]`, round to `precision`, send `Event::SetValue(parsed_value)`, call `event.preventDefault()`.
677	5. **Rejection**: If `parse()` returns `Err`: call `event.preventDefault()` to reject the paste entirely. Optionally announce "Invalid paste content" via a live region.
678	
679	### 3.4 Scrubbing Accessibility
680	
681	During Scrubbing state, the input's `aria-valuenow` updates in real time.
682	Adapters may throttle `aria-valuetext` updates to avoid excessive screen reader
683	announcements.
684	
685	> **Passive wheel listener requirement:** When `allow_mouse_wheel: true`, the adapter attaches a `wheel` event listener with `{ passive: false }` to ensure `preventDefault()` is not silently ignored. This mirrors the passive listener guidance for touch events in `05-interactions.md` §2.4.
686	
687	## 4. Internationalization
688	
689	- **Locale resolution**: The adapter resolves locale from `ArsProvider` and passes it
690	  via `Env.locale` to `Machine::init()`, which stores it in `Context.locale`. All formatting
691	  and parsing uses this resolved locale.
692	- **Decimal separator**: Uses locale-appropriate separator (`,` vs `.`).
693	- **Thousands separator**: Applied when formatting the displayed value.
694	- **`aria-valuetext`**: Adapters derive a memoized formatter from `ArsProvider`
695	  via `use_number_formatter(|| number::FormatOptions::default())` and use it for
696	  locale-aware value text.
697	- **RTL**: Increment/decrement button positions swap visually (CSS `direction` handles this).
698	- **Input parsing**: Must accept both locale-specific input (e.g., `1.234,56` in `de-DE`) and
699	  canonical format (e.g., `1234.56`). On blur, the value is normalized to the canonical `f64`
700	  and the display is re-formatted per locale.
701	
702	### 4.1 Locale-Aware Number Formatting
703	
704	`NumberInput` MUST support locale-aware formatting and parsing of numeric values:
705	
706	- `en-US`: `1,234.56` (comma grouping, dot decimal)
707	- `de-DE`: `1.234,56` (dot grouping, comma decimal)
708	- `fr-FR`: `1 234,56` (narrow no-break space grouping, comma decimal)
709	
710	**Locale Resolution Chain**:
711	
712	1. `locale` prop (highest priority)
713	2. `FormContext.locale` (if inside a Form)
714	3. `ArsProvider` context
715	4. Fallback: `en-US`
716	
717	**Non-Uniform Digit Grouping**: Number formatting and parsing delegate to ICU4X
718	`number::Formatter`, which handles locale-specific grouping (including non-uniform patterns
719	like Indian numbering: `12,34,567`). The component must not hardcode grouping assumptions.
720	When locale is inherited from `ArsProvider`, adapters should resolve this
721	through `use_number_formatter(...)` rather than constructing ad hoc ambient
722	formatters from a thread-local cache.
723	
724	**Negative Number Sign Placement**: Negative number display follows locale conventions via
725	ICU4X — leading minus, trailing minus, or accounting parentheses. Adapters must not hardcode minus sign position.
726	
727	## 5. Form Integration
728	
729	- **Hidden input**: The `Input` part is the native `<input>` element and participates directly in form submission via its `name` attribute. The submitted value is the raw numeric string.
730	- **Validation states**: `aria-invalid="true"` on the Input when `invalid=true`. Native constraint validation is supplemented by the `min`/`max` bounds and `precision` rounding.
731	- **Error message association**: `aria-describedby` on Input points to `Description` (when present) and `ErrorMessage` (when invalid).
732	- **Required**: `aria-required="true"` on Input.
733	- **Reset behavior**: On form reset, the adapter restores `value` to `default_value`.
734	- **Disabled/readonly propagation**: When inside a `Field` or `Fieldset`, the adapter merges `disabled`/`readonly` from `FieldCtx` per `07-forms.md` §12.6.
735	
736	## 6. Library Parity
737	
738	> Compared against: Ark UI (`NumberInput`), React Aria (`NumberField`).
739	
740	### 6.1 Props
741	
742	| Feature                    | ars-ui                                  | Ark UI             | React Aria                                | Notes                                  |
743	| -------------------------- | --------------------------------------- | ------------------ | ----------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
744	| Controlled value           | `value: Option<f64>`                    | `value: string`    | `value: number`                           | Full parity (ars-ui uses numeric type) |
745	| Default value              | `default_value: Option<f64>`            | `defaultValue`     | `defaultValue`                            | Full parity                            |
746	| Min/Max                    | `min`/`max`                             | `min`/`max`        | `minValue`/`maxValue`                     | Full parity                            |
747	| Step                       | `step: f64`                             | `step`             | `step`                                    | Full parity                            |
748	| Large step                 | `large_step: f64`                       | --                 | --                                        | ars-ui enhancement for PageUp/PageDown |
749	| Disabled                   | `disabled: bool`                        | `disabled`         | `isDisabled`                              | Full parity                            |
750	| Read-only                  | `readonly: bool`                        | `readOnly`         | `isReadOnly`                              | Full parity                            |
751	| Required                   | `required: bool`                        | `required`         | `isRequired`                              | Full parity                            |
752	| Invalid                    | `invalid: bool`                         | `invalid`          | `isInvalid`                               | Full parity                            |
753	| Form name                  | `name: Option<String>`                  | `name`             | `name`                                    | Full parity                            |
754	| Form ID                    | `form: Option<String>`                  | `form`             | `form`                                    | Full parity                            |
755	| Mouse wheel                | `allow_mouse_wheel: bool`               | `allowMouseWheel`  | `isWheelDisabled` (inverted)              | Full parity (inverted boolean)         |
756	| Clamp on blur              | `clamp_value_on_blur: bool`             | `clampValueOnBlur` | --                                        | Ark parity                             |
757	| Spin on press              | `spin_on_press: bool`                   | `spinOnPress`      | --                                        | Ark parity                             |
758	| Format options             | `format_options: Option<FormatOptions>` | `formatOptions`    | `formatOptions`                           | Full parity                            |
759	| Locale                     | via `Env.locale` (adapter-resolved)     | `locale`           | --                                        | Ark parity (adapter prop, not core)    |
760	| Increment/decrement labels | via `Messages`                          | `translations`     | `incrementAriaLabel`/`decrementAriaLabel` | Full parity                            |
761	
762	**Gaps:** None.
763	
764	### 6.2 Anatomy
765	
766	| Part             | ars-ui                | Ark UI             | React Aria          | Notes                                                            |
767	| ---------------- | --------------------- | ------------------ | ------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
768	| Root             | `Root`                | `Root`             | `NumberField`       | Full parity                                                      |
769	| Label            | `Label`               | `Label`            | `Label`             | Full parity                                                      |
770	| Input            | `Input`               | `Input`            | `Input`             | Full parity                                                      |
771	| IncrementTrigger | `IncrementTrigger`    | `IncrementTrigger` | `Button[increment]` | Full parity                                                      |
772	| DecrementTrigger | `DecrementTrigger`    | `DecrementTrigger` | `Button[decrement]` | Full parity                                                      |
773	| Scrubber         | -- (scrub via events) | `Scrubber`         | --                  | ars-ui uses Scrubbing state + events instead of a dedicated part |
774	| Control          | --                    | `Control`          | `Group`             | Ark/RA wrapper; ars-ui Root serves this role                     |
775	| ValueText        | --                    | `ValueText`        | --                  | Ark display part; ars-ui uses input value directly               |
776	| Description      | `Description`         | --                 | `Text[description]` | ars-ui form-field part                                           |
777	| ErrorMessage     | `ErrorMessage`        | --                 | `FieldError`        | ars-ui form-field part                                           |
778	
779	**Gaps:** None material. Ark's `Scrubber` is a dedicated part; ars-ui achieves the same via `StartScrub`/`Scrub`/`EndScrub` events on the `Input` element. Ark's `ValueText` is a read-only display; ars-ui formats the value directly in the input.
780	
781	### 6.3 Events
782	
783	| Callback                 | ars-ui                          | Ark UI              | React Aria      | Notes                                  |
784	| ------------------------ | ------------------------------- | ------------------- | --------------- | -------------------------------------- |
785	| Value changed            | `Change(String)`                | `onValueChange`     | `onChange`      | Full parity                            |
786	| Value committed          | via `Blur` + clamp              | `onValueCommit`     | --              | Ark parity                             |
787	| Value invalid (overflow) | via validation                  | `onValueInvalid`    | --              | Ark parity (handled via invalid state) |
788	| Focus change             | `Focus`/`Blur`                  | `onFocusChange`     | `onFocusChange` | Full parity                            |
789	| Scrub                    | `StartScrub`/`Scrub`/`EndScrub` | (via Scrubber part) | --              | Ark parity                             |
790	
791	**Gaps:** None.
792	
793	### 6.4 Features
794	
795	| Feature                 | ars-ui                                  | Ark UI | React Aria   |
796	| ----------------------- | --------------------------------------- | ------ | ------------ |
797	| Keyboard inc/dec        | Yes (arrows, PageUp/PageDown, Home/End) | Yes    | Yes          |
798	| Press-and-hold spin     | Yes                                     | Yes    | Yes          |
799	| Mouse wheel             | Yes                                     | Yes    | Yes (opt-in) |
800	| Scrubbing               | Yes                                     | Yes    | --           |
801	| Locale-aware formatting | Yes                                     | Yes    | Yes          |
802	| Clamp on blur           | Yes                                     | Yes    | --           |
803	| Form integration        | Yes                                     | Yes    | Built-in     |
804	| IME composition         | Yes                                     | --     | --           |
805	
806	**Gaps:** None.
807	
808	### 6.5 Summary
809	
810	- **Overall:** Full parity with both reference libraries.
811	- **Divergences:** ars-ui uses `Option<f64>` for the value type (allowing empty state) instead of Ark's string-based representation. ars-ui adds `large_step` for PageUp/PageDown granularity and IME composition tracking. Scrubbing is handled via events rather than a dedicated `Scrubber` part.
812	- **Recommended additions:** None.
